This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it introduces a new distributed system for training and regularizing large-scale neural networks. It also mentions experiments performed on MNIST handwritten digits classification, which is a common dataset used in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category as the system is designed for distributed computing architectures. 

The cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category is also likely as the paper focuses on training neural networks. 

The cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category is a possibility as the paper may discuss the algorithms and data structures used in the system. 

Finally, the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is a possibility as the experiments are performed on a dataset commonly used in computer vision research.
